{[%evp 0,37,27,27,27,4,6,7,33,27,24,31,25,44,21,-22,-14,-23,46,33,34,40,36,30,
47,56,49,41,74,87,102,83,124,47,54,50,60,92,57,75]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3
b6 4. a3 Ba6 5. Qc2 Bb7 6. Nc3 c5 7. e4 cxd4 8. Nxd4 {Finally, Black can also
play} d6 {It is a slightly passive choice compared to alternatives and overall
the arising version of Hedgehog is very comofortable for White. After normal
developing moves for both sides:} 9. Be2 Be7 (9... Nbd7 {should transpose to
the main line after} 10. O-O Be7 11. Be3 O-O ({or} 11... a6 12. f4 Qc7 13. Rad1
O-O) 12. Rad1) 10. O-O O-O 11. Be3 Nbd7 12. Rad1 a6 {We reach an important
position. Some players prefer to support the f3-pawn and keep manoeuvring, but
the most ambitious and principled approach is:} 13. f4 {This way, White starts
the kingside attack with g2-g4-g5, which can be quite unpleasant for Black
considering his lack of space. The e4-pawn can be defended with Bf3 if needed.
} Qc7 ({One game featured} 13... g6 {but in this case I believe that White is
ready to open the position on kingside with:} 14. f5 $1 $146 {This not only
puts pressure on e6 pawn but also opens the way for the dark-squared bishop and
the f-file.} gxf5 15. exf5 e5 16. Nf3 {and after} Kh8 17. Bh6 Rg8 {White can
neutralize potential threats along the g-file with:} 18. Ng5 Qe8 19. Bf3 Bxf3
20. Nxf3 {with obviously better chances.}) 14. g4 Nc5 ({Another game saw:} 
14... Rfd8 {but after} 15. g5 Ne8 16. f5 $1 {White generated powerful attack
very easily} exf5 17. Nxf5 Bf8 18. Qd2 Nc5 {Volodin,A (2433)-Erturan,Y (2366)
Plovdiv 2010 and now after} 19. Rf4 $1 $146 {White would secure an overwhelming
advantage by dominating on absolutely all fronts. Bd4 and Rdf1 could follow
and Black could hardly come up with a constructive plan.}) 15. Bf3 h6 {This
position was reached in Pototschnig, M (1831)-Vegjeleki, A (2249) ICCF email
2010.} ({Pretty bad was} 15... Rae8 $2 {in the game Banikas,H (2445)-Lobron,E 
(2585) Yerevan 1996. After} 16. b4 Ncd7 17. g5 {Black loses his knight.}) {
After accurate:} 16. Qg2 $146 Nh7 17. g5 hxg5 18. fxg5 g6 19. h4 {White's
advantage is obvious. He has full control of the centre and a promising
attacking setup on the kingside.} *

